			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When you say &quot;get-then-clear&quot; do you mean &quot;get-then-in-the-next-clock-cycle-clear&quot;?<br /><br />It's not possible in hardware to have a counter that you increment _and_ clear in the same cycle. It can only do one or the other in each clock cycle, not both. If it's the case that it just clears in the next clock cycle (which is what I think you mean) then that's really easy to do.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
